{"tid":1932357,"cid":15,"subCid":0,"title":"WeWork遭調查 軟銀據報放棄234億港元增持","createTime":"2020-03-18T16:20:46.000Z","updateTime":"2020-03-19T02:12:56.000Z","uid":71237,"like":1,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":3,"replies":[{"pid":"e7b4696d2a6d78dcaac79ed1b554b8ed87338630","tid":1932357,"uid":71237,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-18T16:20:46.000Z","msg":"2020-03-19<br />\nWeWork遭調查 軟銀據報放棄234億增持<br />\n<br />\n《華爾街日報》引述消息人士稱，日本軟銀(SoftBank)可能取消部分原本公布、拯救共享辦公室營運商WeWork的計劃，原因是監管機構對WeWork展開調查。<br />\n<br />\n根據報道，軟銀周二向WeWork股東發出通知，表示因應美國證券交易委員會(SEC)與司法部對WeWork展開的調查，原定向全體WeWork股東提出的30億美元(234億港元)股份收購計劃，很可能不再進行。<br />\n<br />\n如果軟銀放棄收購WeWork，WeWork前行政總裁諾伊曼(Adam Neumann)將不能透過這項售股計劃，套現最多9.7億美元。<br />\n<br />\n不過，軟銀不會改變向WeWork直接注資50億美元的計劃，其中15億美元的注資已經完成。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www2.hkej.com/instantnews/international/article/2406565\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.hkej.com%2Finstantnews%2Finternational%2Farticle%2F2406565&d=AthmRk%2BBSDjaWf6zT95BzOrkGmmZttFFipzpmUasbQ8%3D&h=9a698360\" target=\"_blank\">https://www2.hkej.com/instantnews/international/article/2406565</a>"},{"pid":"f0665e4cf52fd028ec390cd1243c4e7543fd853e","tid":1932357,"uid":136527,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-18T16:44:29.000Z","msg":"Omg<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"abca6faa66897e5ac7aeb1d17fe287a03ba8ea77","tid":1932357,"uid":28068,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-19T02:12:56.000Z","msg":"wework靠乜做到咁大?<br />\n唔覺有咩特別"}]}